{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_019R3kFpqanAF8ridcgVZm1a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Es9TDQPf3NedsZAii36MzQ","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Architecture & design review","subagent_type":"code-review-expert","prompt":"Review the architecture and design of the changes in lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts.\n\n## Context\nThis is iteration 28 of a title extraction optimization loop for a React Native recipe photo app. The code extracts recipe titles from OCR text using heuristics + semantic embeddings. It runs on mobile (must complete under 10 seconds total).\n\n## The improvement plan is at tools/title-loop/docs/28-1ac016c/improvement-plan.md — read it for the planned fixes.\n\n## Changes (read the diff carefully)\nThe diff from HEAD~1 implements 4 fixes:\n1. **Dual-variant blind OCR repair** — generates both `1→i` and `1→l` variants instead of always choosing `l`. Adds `hasErraticCasing`/`normalizeErraticCasing` for cases like `KoPyTka`.\n2. **Direct-successor bonus skips blank lines** — scans backward past blank lines to find section headers.\n3. **Broadened overflow marker regex** — matches more natural corruption markers like `CORRUPTED TEXT` and `PARTIAL RECIPE`.\n4. **Unified body-content prologue detector** — replaces separate instruction/prose prologue checks with a unified one that handles interleaving.\n\nAlso:\n- `buildCandidates` now returns `{ candidates, burstEnd }` instead of just the array\n- `isTitleAbsentPage` accepts a `startFrom` parameter to skip burst lines\n- `passesCorroboration` accepts a `startLine` parameter\n- `normalizeOcrTitle` refactored to use shared `applyBlindOcrRepair`\n- Subset dedup logic enhanced to protect multi-line joins with food-category suffixes\n\n## Focus Areas\n1. Is the `buildCandidates` return type change clean? Does the burstEnd threading through the pipeline make sense?\n2. Does the unified prologue detector properly replace the two separate checks without regression risk?\n3. Is the erratic casing detection (`hasErraticCasing`) well-calibrated? Could it produce false positives?\n4. Does the subset dedup enhancement (food-category suffix protection) create any edge cases?\n5. Is the overall flow coherent — do the 4 fixes compose well without unintended interactions?\n\nRead the source file and the improvement plan, then provide your assessment."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1998,"cache_read_input_tokens":40068,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1998},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"66d6120a-7fee-4673-bb0a-75db3320d34d","uuid":"f93f8101-50ac-45c3-a82b-871e5d375ca2"}
