{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Review code quality and maintainability of the changes in lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts.\n\n## Context\nThis is a recipe title extractor for a React Native app. The diff (HEAD~1 to HEAD, plus unstaged changes) implements 4 fixes from an improvement plan.\n\nRead the full file at lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts and focus on:\n\n1. **Naming quality** — Are `applyBlindOcrRepairToken`, `generateBlindOcrVariants`, `hasErraticCasing`, `normalizeErraticCasing` clear and descriptive?\n2. **Code duplication** — The old `normalizeOcrTitle` had inline OCR repair logic that's now extracted to `applyBlindOcrRepair`. Is the refactoring clean? Any remaining duplication?\n3. **Function complexity** — `buildCandidates` is already long. Does the new blind OCR repair block (lines ~657-688) add too much inline complexity? Should it be extracted?\n4. **Comment quality** — Are the new comments helpful or noise? Do they explain \"why\" not just \"what\"?\n5. **Magic numbers** — Check for unexplained constants (thresholds, regex patterns).\n6. **The subset dedup enhancement** (around line 1507-1530) — is the logic readable? The nested conditions with `startsWith` and `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS` check.\n7. **Dead code or unused paths** — Did the refactoring leave anything orphaned?\n\nProvide specific line references and suggestions."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DWZvkYLSgR3KWoyc1JyPBq","session_id":"66d6120a-7fee-4673-bb0a-75db3320d34d","uuid":"c1673fad-21d1-4313-9690-b0940f22c956"}
